%2Fall-ryan-murphy-tv-shows-ranked-from-worst-to-best-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ERyan%20Murphy's%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3Eanthology%20series%2C%20dramatizes%20the%20fallout%20between%20author%20Truman%20Capote%20and%20some%20of%20New%20York's%20most%20legendary%20socialites%2C%20whom%20he%20referred%20to%20in%20his%20final%2C%20unfinished%20novel%20as%20%26quot%3Bswans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20audiences%20learn%20in%20the%20first%20episode%20of%20the%20series%2C%20which%20aired%20Wednesday%2C%20Capote%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftom-hollander-tom-holland-avengers-marvel-paycheck-7-figures-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ETom%20Hollander%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E)%20sees%20these%20beautiful%2C%20wealthy%20women%20as%20swans%20because%20they%20glide%20through%20society%20in%20a%20way%20that%20appears%20effortless%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20if%20you%20glimpse%20below%20the%20surface%2C%20you%20would%20see%20that%20the%20swans%20have%20to%20paddle%20faster%20than%20everyone%20else%20just%20to%20stay%20afloat.%20If%20they%20don't%2C%20they'll%20drown%20underneath%20the%20heavy%20weight%20of%20their%20plumage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20real%20life%20as%20in%20the%20show%2C%20Capote%20was%20a%20trusted%20confidant%C3%A9%20to%20these%20women%20and%20learned%20about%20all%20the%20ways%20they%20were%20struggling%3A%20marital%20issues%2C%20infidelity%2C%20substance%20abuse%2C%20and%20sexual%20assault%2C%20among%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20betrayed%20this%20trust%20by%20writing%20a%20searing%20commentary%20that%20included%20thinly%20veiled%20portraits%20of%20many%20of%20these%20women%20for%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.esquire.com%2Fentertainment%2Fa40376194%2Ftruman-capote-la-cote-basque%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EEsquire%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20story%20titled%20%26quot%3BLa%20C%C3%B4te%20Basque%201965%2C%26quot%3B%20everything%20changed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20short%20story%20(which%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20an%20excerpt%20of%20his%20forthcoming%20magnum%20opus%20%26quot%3BAnswered%20Prayers%26quot%3B)%20was%20published%20in%201975%2C%20Capote%20was%20cast%20out%20of%20their%20inner%20circle%20and%2C%20in%20many%20cases%2C%20was%20never%20allowed%20back%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20everything%20you%20need%20to%20know%20about%20Capote's%20swans%20featured%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20ones%20that%20didn't%20make%20his%20inner%20circle%20but%20still%20had%20their%20secrets%20exposed%20in%20his%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBabe%20Paley%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Naomi%20Watts%20as%20Babe%20Paley%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B%3B%20%20Barbara%20%26quot%3BBabe%26quot%3B%20Paley%20in%201967.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bb85e97a3d27148876761d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ENaomi%20Watts%20as%20Babe%20Paley%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B%3B%20Barbara%20%26quot%3BBabe%26quot%3B%20Paley%20in%201967.%3Cp%3EFX%2C%20CBS%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBabe%20Paley%20had%20only%20one%20fault%3A%20she%20was%20perfect.%20Otherwise%2C%20she%20was%20perfect%2C%26quot%3B%20Capote%20once%20remarked%20of%20the%20woman%20said%20to%20have%20been%20his%20favorite%20swan%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tatler.com%2Farticle%2Fwho-was-babe-paley-feud-truman-capote-vs-the-swans%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETatler%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPaley%20(portrayed%20by%20Naomi%20Watts%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B)%20was%20one%20of%20New%20York's%20most%20famous%20socialites.%20Born%20to%20a%20famed%20neurosurgeon%2C%20she%20made%20her%20debut%20as%20a%20debutante%20in%201934%2C%20and%20four%20years%20later%2C%20Paley%2C%20then%20known%20by%20her%20maiden%20name%2C%20Barbara%20Cushing%2C%20began%20working%20as%20a%20fashion%20editor%20at%20Vogue%20magazine%2C%20according%20to%20an%20obituary%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1978%2F07%2F07%2Farchives%2Fbarbara-cushing-paley-dies-at-63-style-pacesetter-in-three-decades.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20left%20Vogue%20and%20became%20a%20full-time%20socialite%20in%201948%20but%20was%20still%20widely%20known%20for%20her%20impeccable%20style.%20She%20was%20inducted%20into%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanityfair.com%2Fstyle%2F2009%2F08%2Fhall-of-fame-women%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInternational%20Best%20Dressed%20List%20Hall%20of%20Fame%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201958%20after%20becoming%20a%20permanent%20fixture%20on%20the%20world's%20best%E2%80%90dressed%20women%20list.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20married%20twice.%20Her%20first%20husband%20was%20advertising%20executive%20and%20oil%20heir%20Stanley%20Mortimer%2C%20with%20whom%20she%20had%20two%20children%3B%20her%20second%20was%20CBS%20founder%20William%20Paley%2C%20with%20whom%20she%20welcomed%20two%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECapote's%20%26quot%3BLa%20C%C3%B4te%20Basque%2C%201965%26quot%3B%20alluded%20to%20Paley%20and%20her%20husband's%20martial%20issues%20stemming%20from%20his%20infidelities%20in%20the%20characters%20Cleo%20Dillon%20and%20her%20philandering%20husband%2C%20Sidney%20Dillon.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fculture%2Farticle%2F20240125-feud-capote-vs-the-swans-how-a-scandalous-truman-capote-story-exposed-the-secrets-of-us-high-society%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBBC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20after%20the%20magazine%20hit%20newsstands%2C%20Paley%20never%20spoke%20to%20Capote%20again.%20She%20died%20at%20the%20age%20of%2063%20from%20lung%20cancer%20in%201978.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ESlim%20Keith%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Diane%20Lane%20as%20Slim%20Keith%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B%3B%20Nancy%20%26quot%3BSlim%26quot%3B%20Keith%2C%20circa%201949.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bb86b3ac2de4f17ee6847a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDiane%20Lane%20as%20Slim%20Keith%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B%3B%20Nancy%20%26quot%3BSlim%26quot%3B%20Keith%2C%20circa%201949.%3Cp%3EFX%2C%20Bettmann%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwwd.com%2Fpop-culture%2Fculture-news%2Ftruman-capote-feud-swans-lee-radziwill-babe-paley-1236022236%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWomen's%20Wear%20Daily%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Nancy%20Keith%20(portrayed%20by%20Diane%20Lane)%2C%20who%20graced%20the%20cover%20of%20Harper's%20Bazaar%20at%2022%2C%20didn't%20get%20her%20nickname%20%26quot%3BSlim%26quot%3B%20from%20her%20self-confessed%20%26quot%3Btall%2C%20skinny%20frame%26quot%3B%20but%20because%20of%20a%20chance%20encounter%20the%20California%20native%20had%20with%20actor%20William%20Powell.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20vacationing%20in%20Death%20Valley%2C%20Powell%20spotted%20Keith%20diving%20into%20a%20pool%20and%20christened%20Keith%20with%20the%20moniker%20that%20would%20follow%20her%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20her%20life%2C%20so%20the%20story%20goes.%20After%20striking%20up%20a%20friendship%2C%20Powell%20introduced%20Keith%20to%20his%20Hollywood%20friends%2C%20including%20%26quot%3BScarface%26quot%3B%20director%20Howard%20Hawks%2C%20who%20was%20so%20smitten%20with%20her%20that%20he%20divorced%20his%20wife%20and%20begged%20Keith%20to%20marry%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKeith's%20influence%20on%20Hawk%20and%20Hollywood%20can't%20be%20overstated%3B%20the%20filmmaker%20reportedly%20modeled%20several%20of%20his%20iconic%20femme%20fatales%20after%20Keith%2C%20and%20she%20was%20even%20responsible%20for%20the%20discovery%20of%20Lauren%20Bacall%20as%20she%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vogue.com%2Farticle%2Fslim-keith-summer-style-inspiration%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espotted%20her%20on%20the%20cover%20of%20a%20magazine%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20encouraged%20her%20then-husband%20to%20cast%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHawks%20wasn't%20the%20only%20man%20in%20Keith's%20life%3B%20she%20was%20also%20pursued%20romantically%20by%20Clark%20Gable%20and%20Ernest%20Hemingway%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.vanityfair.com%2Farticle%2F1990%2F6%2Fforever-slim%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVanity%20Fair.%3C%2Fa%3E%20She%20remarried%20twice.%20Her%20second%20husband%20was%20American%20producer%20Leland%20Hayward%2C%20and%20her%20third%20was%20the%20British%20banker%20and%20aristocrat%20Kenneth%20Keith%2C%20Baron%20Keith%20of%20Castleacre%2C%20which%20made%20her%20Lady%20Keith%20of%20Castleacre.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20widely%20believed%20that%20the%20fictional%20Lady%20Ina%20Coolbirth%20in%20%26quot%3BLa%20C%C3%B4te%20Basque%2C%201965%26quot%3B%20was%20a%20thinly%20veiled%20portrait%20of%20Keith%2C%20bolstered%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20real%20Keith%20was%20the%20only%20one%20of%20Capote's%20so-called%20swans%20with%20a%20title.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1990%2F04%2F07%2Fobituaries%2Fnancy-lady-keith-is-dead-at-73-a-socialite-known-for-her-wit.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EShe%20died%20at%2072%20in%201990%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20having%20never%20spoken%20to%20the%20author%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EC.Z.%20Guest%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chlo%C3%AB%20Sevigny%20as%20C.Z.%20Guest%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%3B%20C.Z.%20Guest%2C%20circa%201953.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bb85b9ac2de4f17ee68446%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChlo%C3%AB%20Sevigny%20as%20C.Z.%20Guest%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%3B%20C.Z.%20Guest%2C%20circa%201953.%3Cp%3EFX%2C%20Slim%20Aarons%2FHulton%20Archive%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20Capote%20states%20in%20the%20first%20episode%20of%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%2C%26quot%3B%20Lucy%20Douglas%20%26quot%3BC.Z.%26quot%3B%20Guest%20(played%20by%20Chlo%C3%AB%20Sevigny)%20was%20a%20master%20horticulturist%20who%20could%20stretch%20marigold%20season%20into%20autumn.%20But%20that%20wasn't%20her%20only%20notable%20talent.%20Guest%20was%20also%20a%20skilled%20horsewoman%2C%20actor%2C%20and%20columnist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20also%20a%20muse%20to%20several%20fashion%20designers%20and%20artists%2C%20including%20Diego%20Rivera%2C%20Salvador%20Dal%C3%AD%2C%20Ralph%20Lauren%2C%20and%20Andy%20Warhol.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20was%20married%20to%20polo%20champion%20Winston%20Frederick%20Churchill%20Guest%2C%20a%20distant%20cousin%20of%20the%20British%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20until%20his%20death%20in%201972%20and%20never%20remarried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20obituary%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.google.com%2Fnewspapers%3Fid%3DcpY1AAAAIBAJ%26pg%3D426%2C4265879%26dq%3Dcz%2Bguest%26hl%3Den%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EObserver-Reporter%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Guest's%20distinctive%20nickname%2C%20%26quot%3BC.Z.%26quot%3B%20was%20adapted%20from%20%26quot%3BSissy%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20name%20her%20siblings%20would%20often%20call%20her%20when%20they%20were%20young.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGuest%2C%20who%20died%20in%202003%20at%2083%2C%20was%20one%20of%20the%20few%20who%20didn't%20shun%20Capote%20after%20he%20wrote%20%26quot%3BLa%20C%C3%B4te%20Basque%2C%26quot%3B%20likely%20because%20she%20wasn't%20easily%20identifiable%20in%20the%20text.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELee%20Radziwill%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Calista%20Flockhart%20as%20Lee%20Radziwill%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B%3B%20Lee%20Radziwill%20circa%201968.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bb8785ac2de4f17ee68497%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECalista%20Flockhart%20as%20Lee%20Radziwill%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B%3B%20Lee%20Radziwill%20circa%201968.%3Cp%3EFX%2C%20Bettmann%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELee%20Radziwill%20was%20one%20of%20Capote's%20most%20well-connected%20swans%20as%20the%20younger%20sister%20of%20Jacqueline%20Onassis%20and%20sister-in-law%20of%20President%20John%20F.%20Kennedy.%20But%20even%20before%20her%20sibling's%20marriage%2C%20she%20was%20a%20person%20of%20note%2C%20having%20been%20born%20into%20a%20socially%20established%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20coming-out%20party%20in%201950%20was%20documented%20in%20Life%20magazine%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.townandcountrymag.com%2Fleisure%2Farts-and-culture%2Fa46541533%2Ffeud-capote-vs-the-swans-history-explained%2F%23lee-radziwill%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETown%20%26amp%3B%20Country%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20the%20years%20that%20followed%2C%20Raziwill%20attempted%20to%20break%20into%20the%20movie%20business%20but%20was%20unsuccessful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Gerald%20Clarke's%20biography%20of%20Capote%2C%20even%20before%20Capote's%20Esquire%20piece%20was%20published%2C%20Radziwill's%20relationship%20with%20the%20author%20was%20strained%20as%20he%20had%20pushed%20for%20her%20to%20star%20in%20a%20television%20adaptation%20of%20the%201944%20movie%20%26quot%3BLaura%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20he%20had%20written.%20The%20project%20was%20not%20well%20received%20by%20critics%2C%20and%20Radziwill%20never%20acted%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERadziwill%20married%20three%20times.%20Her%20first%20husband%20was%20Michael%20Temple%20Canfield%2C%20a%20publishing%20executive.%20Upon%20her%20second%20marriage%20to%20Polish%20aristocrat%20Stanis%C5%82aw%20Albrecht%20Radziwi%C5%82%C5%82%2C%20she%20became%20a%20princess%2C%20but%20in%20title%20only.%20Her%20third%20marriage%2C%20to%20movie%20director%20and%20choreographer%20Herbert%20Ross%2C%20ended%20in%20divorce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20other%20women%2C%20Radziwill%20and%20her%20former%20First%20Lady%20sister%20are%20mentioned%20by%20name%20in%20Capote's%20Esquire%20story%2C%20rather%20than%20given%20an%20alias.%20After%20it%20was%20published%2C%20she%20continued%20her%20acquaintance%20with%20the%20%26quot%3BIn%20Cold%20Blood%26quot%3B%20author%2C%20likely%20because%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fculture%2Farticle%2F20240125-feud-capote-vs-the-swans-how-a-scandalous-truman-capote-story-exposed-the-secrets-of-us-high-society%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBBC%3C%2Fa%3E%20points%20out%2C%20the%20two%20main%20characters%20in%20the%20story%20conclude%20that%20she%20is%20more%20beautiful%20than%20her%20sister.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERadziwill%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vogue.com%2Farticle%2Flee-radziwill-obituary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edied%20in%202019%20at%20age%2085.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EAnn%20Woodward%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Demi%20Moore%20as%20Ann%20Woodward%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B%3B%20Ann%20Woodward%20in%201955.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65baae9043bb77284ba2450e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDemi%20Moore%20as%20Ann%20Woodward%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B%3B%20Ann%20Woodward%20in%201955.%3Cp%3EPari%20Dukovic%2FFX%2C%20Bettmann%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAnn%20Woodward%20(Demi%20Moore)%20was%20not%20technically%20one%20of%20Capote's%20swans%2C%20but%20his%20pen%20did%20take%20aim%20at%20her%20in%20the%20Esquire%20story%2C%20creating%20a%20thinly%20veiled%20character%20named%20Ann%20Hopkins%20who%2C%20like%20Woodward%2C%20accidentally%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffeud-capote-vs-swans-ann-woodward-suicide-death-real-story-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20killed%20her%20husband%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20night%20%3C%2Fa%3Eafter%20mistaking%20him%20for%20an%20intruder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20real%20life%2C%20Woodward%2C%20who%20entered%20into%20society%20from%20obscurity%20after%20marrying%20banking%20heir%20William%20Woodward%20Jr.%2C%20was%20exonerated%20for%20her%20husband's%20death%20after%20testifying%20that%20there%20had%20been%20a%20string%20of%20break-ins%20in%20their%20Oyster%20Bay%20neighborhood%20and%20they%20had%20both%20gone%20to%20bed%20armed%20with%20weapons.%20Per%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F1975%2F10%2F12%2Farchives%2Fann-woodward-cleared-in-55-of-slaying-her-husband-dead.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%20obituary%2C%20a%20man%20even%20pleaded%20guilty%20to%20attempted%20burglary%20of%20the%20Woodward%20estate%20on%20the%20night%20of%20the%20shooting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20character%20in%20Capote's%20story%20%E2%80%94%20which%20was%20published%2020%20years%20after%20the%20shooting%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bgot%20away%20with%20cold-blooded%20murder%26quot%3B%20after%20deciding%20she%20would%20get%20more%20of%20her%20husband's%20estate%20as%20a%20widow%20than%20a%20divorc%C3%A9e.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShortly%20before%20the%20issue%20of%20Esquire%20carrying%20the%20story%20hit%20newsstands%2C%20Woodward%20killed%20herself%20by%20ingesting%20a%20cyanide%20pill.%20There%20is%20no%20evidence%20that%20Woodward%20knew%20the%20excerpt%20would%20try%20to%20paint%20her%20as%20a%20murderous%2C%20gold-digging%20wife%20but%20it%20has%20been%20heavily%20speculated%20over%20the%20years%20that%20she%20had%20received%20an%20advance%20copy%20of%20the%20story.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EJoanne%20Carson%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Molly%20Ringwald%20as%20Joanne%20Carson%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B%3B%20Joanne%20Carson%20in%201972.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bb885a43bb77284ba26167%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMolly%20Ringwald%20as%20Joanne%20Carson%20in%20%26quot%3BFeud%3A%20Capote%20vs.%20The%20Swans%26quot%3B%3B%20Joanne%20Carson%20in%201972.%3Cp%3EFX%2C%20Michael%20Ochs%20Archives%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EJoanne%20Carson%2C%20the%20ex-wife%20of%20the%20%26quot%3BTonight%20Show%26quot%3B%20host%20Johnny%20Carson%2C%20was%20also%20not%20officially%20one%20of%20Capote's%20swans%20but%20among%20those%20satirized%20in%20the%20piece.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20thinly%20veiled%20counterpart%20was%20Jane%20Baxter%2C%20the%20wife%20of%20a%20%26quot%3Bmidnight-TV%20clown%26quot%3B%20who%20the%20two%20gossiping%20women%20say%20received%20a%20phone%20call%20from%20her%20husband%20while%20he%20was%20in%20bed%20with%20his%20mistress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20having%20her%20laundry%20aired%20so%20publicly%2C%20she%20remained%20a%20loyal%20and%20longtime%20friend%20to%20Capote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20that%20she%20forgave%20Capote%20for%20his%20less-than-flattering%20portrait%20of%20her%20marriage%20because%20of%20the%20loyalty%20he%20had%20shown%20after%20her%20divorce%20from%20the%20TV%20legend%20in%201972.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEveryone%20moved%20toward%20Johnny%20%5Bafter%20the%20divorce%5D%2C%20because%20that%20was%20where%20the%20power%20was%2C%26quot%3B%20Carson%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Farchives%2Fla-xpm-2006-oct-31-et-capote31-story.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELos%20Angeles%20Times%3