20at%20the%20time%20%E2%80%94%20requested%20that%20the%20judge%20bar%20evidence%20of%20the%20affair%20from%20entering%20court.%20The%20defense%20argued%20that%20evidence%20of%20adultery%20is%20irrelevant%20to%20the%20charges%20the%20couple%20faces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20argued%20that%20evidence%20of%20the%20infidelity%20was%20relevant%20because%20the%20Crumbleys%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bduty%26quot%3B%20to%20protect%20their%20community%20from%20their%20son%20and%20%26quot%3Bwhat%20they%20exposed%20their%20son%20to%26quot%3B%20should%20be%20relevant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%2C%20the%20judge%20ruled%20that%20evidence%20of%20the%20affair%20would%20not%20be%20allowed%20at%20trial.%20But%20that%20ruling%20was%20reversed%20on%20Wednesday%20after%20Brian%20Meloche%20%E2%80%94%20the%20firefighter%20with%20whom%20Jennifer%20Crumbley%20was%20having%20the%20affair%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D-HLIUTH82ag%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Etestified%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20During%20Meloche's%20testimony%2C%20Crumbley's%20attorneys%20started%20a%20line%20of%20questioning%20that%20the%20judge%20said%20opened%20the%20door%20to%20questions%20about%20the%20affair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20asked%20the%20jury%20to%20leave%20after%20Shannon%20Smith%2C%20a%20defense%20attorney%20for%20Crumbley%2C%20asked%20Meloche%20if%20police%20told%20him%20he%20would%20be%20in%20trouble%20if%20he%20helped%20Crumbley.%20Smith%20said%20Meloche%20was%20initially%20holding%20back%20because%20police%20%26quot%3Bput%20pressure%20on%20him%20and%20made%20him%20fear%20he'd%20lose%20his%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecutors%20argued%20that%20Smith's%20line%20of%20questioning%20opened%20the%20door%20to%20evidence%20about%20the%20affair%20because%20they%20say%20the%20reason%20Meloche%20was%20hesitant%20to%20speak%20to%20police%20was%20because%20he%20didn't%20want%20the%20relationship%20to%20be%20made%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudge%20Julie%20Nicholson%20then%20asked%20Crumbley%20to%20stand%20and%20attest%20that%20she%20understood%20that%20she%20was%20reversing%20her%20previous%20ruling%20that%20evidence%20of%20her%20affair%20was%20irrelevant%20to%20the%20trial%20due%20to%20her%20attorney's%20line%20of%20questioning.%20Crumbley%20responded%20that%20she%20trusted%20her%20attorney%20and%20said%20she%20was%20willing%20to%20let%20the%20evidence%20be%20shown%20to%20jurors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicholson%20said%20she%20would%20allow%20Meloche%20to%20answer%20questions%20about%20the%20affair%20but%20would%20keep%20a%20tight%20leash%20on%20the%20attorneys.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe's%20isn't%20charged%20with%20being%20immoral%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicholson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20a%20trial%20about%20her%20morality%2C%20so%20I%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20we%20stick%20to%20the%20case%20and%20the%20elements%20you%20are%20required%20to%20prove%2C%20which%20is%20not%20that%20she's%20a%20bad%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicholson%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjennifer-crumbley-james-crumbley-affair-oxford-school-shooting-michigan-trial-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706826677000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bc051843bb77284ba2c315%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjennifer-crumbley-james-crumbley-affair-oxford-school-shooting-michigan-trial-2024-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jennifer%20and%20James%20Crumbley%2C%20the%20parents%20of%20a%20Michigan%20school%20shooter%2C%20are%20on%20trial%20for%20related%20involuntary%20manslaughter%20charges.%20It%20is%20the%20first%20time%20the%20parents%20of%20a%20school%20shooter%20are%20standing%20trial.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kniemeyer%40insider.com%20(Kenneth%20Niemeyer)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.