%20to%20the%20elderly%2C%20women%20and%20persons%20with%20disabilities%20in%20the%20below%20poverty%20line%20(BPL)%20category.%20The%20minimal%20allocations%20made%20to%20NSAP%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20budget%20are%20both%20unsurprising%20and%20consistent%20with%20a%20decade-long%20pattern%20characterised%20by%20poor%20implementation%2C%20and%20restricted%20funding.%20This%20trend%20indicates%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20reluctance%20to%20meaningfully%20address%20the%20issues%20of%20social%20security%20and%20economic%20protection%20for%20vulnerable%20and%20marginalised%20populations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EReducing%20budgetary%20allocations%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20budget%20for%20NSAP%20increased%20by%20Rs%2016%20crore%2C%20from%20Rs.%209636%20crore%20(BE)%20in%20FY%202023-24%20to%20Rs.%209652%20crore%20in%20the%20current%20budget.%20While%20it%20looks%20like%20a%20marginal%20increase%2C%20however%2C%20this%20is%20a%20decline%20in%20real%20terms%20when%20indexed%20to%20inflation.%20As%20a%20percentage%20share%20of%20the%20total%20budget%20outlay%2C%20the%20allocation%20to%20NSAP%20has%20steadily%20decreased%20in%20the%20last%20decade%2C%20reducing%20from%200.58%25%20in%20FY%202014-15%20to%20just%200.20%25%20in%20FY%202024-25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184528%2Funnamed-1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184528%2Funnamed-1.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184528%2Funnamed-1-300x188.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184528%2Funnamed-1-1024x642.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695272%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22752%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Union%20Budget%20FY%202013-2014%20to%20FY%202023-25%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2Fe%2F2PACX-1vR1QBlW64dyq5bYPv4_nmqAavHvaLSvhv1RRvgCOGY0i-KWbC0FONQAGygtgCc6PVPZECojIs4JRBuF%2Fpubhtml%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20corresponding%20numbers)%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20total%20budget%20outlay%20nearly%20tripling%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20the%20budget%20allocated%20to%20NSAP%20has%20remained%20stagnant%20at%20approximately%20Rs.9500%20crore.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20decrease%20is%20notable%2C%20especially%20considering%20the%20expansion%20of%20coverage%20under%20the%20three%20primary%20sub-schemes%20of%20NSAP%20has%20increased%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faccountabilityindia.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fnsap.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E2.12%20crore%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20individuals%20to%202.97%20crore%20individuals%20during%20the%20same%20period.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Finterim-union-budget-follows-tradition-of-modi-governments-apathy-towards-most-vulnerable%5C%22%3EInterim%20Union%20Budget%20Follows%20Tradition%20of%20Modi%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Apathy%20Towards%20Most%20Vulnerable%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20expenditure%20trend%20over%20the%20past%20decade%20shows%20that%20the%20actual%20expenditure%20is%20consistently%20lower%20than%20the%20budget%20and%20revised%20estimates.%20Between%20FY%202014-15%20and%20FY%202022-23%2C%20there%20has%20been%20an%20average%20underspending%20of%20Rs%20331%20crore%20in%20the%20past%20nine%20years.%20Underspending%20has%20ranged%20from%20Rs%20646%20crore%20in%20FY%202016-17%20to%20Rs%20473%20crore%20in%20FY%202021-22.%20This%20indicates%20that%20funds%20allocated%20for%20NSAP%20are%20not%20fully%20utilised%2C%20largely%20due%20to%20mismanagement%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20transparency%20in%20the%20process%20of%20disbursal%20of%20funds%20at%20the%20state%20and%20central%20levels.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOnly%20during%20the%20first%20year%20of%20the%20pandemic%2C%20in%20FY%202020-2021%2C%20the%20budget%20was%20revised%20nearly%20fivefold%20from%20Rs%209196%20crores%20to%20Rs.%204%2C2617%20crores%20when%20a%20one-time%20payment%20of%20Rs%201%2C000%20was%20made%20to%20NSAP%20beneficiaries.%20However%2C%20the%20budgetary%20allocation%20for%20the%20subsequent%20years%20show%20only%20a%20nominal%20increase%20even%20though%20millions%20of%20people%20are%20still%20recovering%20from%20the%20economic%20shock%20of%20the%20pandemic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184538%2Funnamed-2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184538%2Funnamed-2.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184538%2Funnamed-2-300x163.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184538%2Funnamed-2-1024x555.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695273%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Union%20Budget%20FY%202013-2014%20to%20FY%202023-25%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.google.com%2Fspreadsheets%2Fd%2Fe%2F2PACX-1vR1QBlW64dyq5bYPv4_nmqAavHvaLSvhv1RRvgCOGY0i-KWbC0FONQAGygtgCc6PVPZECojIs4JRBuF%2Fpubhtml%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20corresponding%20numbers)%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIncreased%20fiscal%20burden%20on%20states%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20NSAP%20is%20one%20of%20the%20six%20%E2%80%98core%20of%20the%20core%E2%80%99%20centrally%20sponsored%20schemes%20(CSS)%20under%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Rural%20Development.%20According%20to%20the%202014%20Guidelines%2C%20the%20NSAP%20is%20designed%20to%20provide%20monetary%20assistance%20from%20the%20Union%20Government%20for%20three%20distinct%20demographics%20in%20the%20BPL%20category.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUnder%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20National%20Old%20Age%20Pension%20Scheme%20(IGNOAPS)%2C%20assistance%20of%20Rs%20200%20per%20month%20is%20provided%20for%20the%20elderly%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2060%20and%2079%20and%20Rs%20500%20per%20month%20for%20those%20aged%2079%20and%20above.%20For%20widows%2C%20a%20sum%20of%20Rs%20300%20per%20month%20is%20provided%20under%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20National%20Widow%20Pension%20Scheme%20(IGNWPS).%20For%20persons%20with%20disabilities%2C%20Rs%20300%20is%20provided%20for%20those%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2018%20to%2079%2C%20and%20Rs%20500%20for%20those%20above%20the%20age%20of%2079%20under%20the%20Indira%20Gandhi%20National%20Disability%20Pension%20Scheme%20(IGNDPS).%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20contribution%20from%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20old-age%20pensions%20has%20remained%20unchanged%20since%202007%3B%20for%20widow%20and%20disability%20pensions%2C%20this%20amount%20was%20last%20increased%20to%20Rs%20300%20in%202011.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20CSS%2C%20the%20funding%20for%20this%20programme%20is%20shared%20between%20the%20Union%20and%20states.%20Under%20NSAP%2C%20pension%20amounts%20across%20all%20sub-schemes%20are%20also%20supplemented%20with%20an%20additional%20contribution%20from%20the%20states.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20this%20regard%2C%20the%20guidelines%20recommend%20that%20the%20states%20at%20minimum%20match%20their%20contribution%20to%20that%20of%20the%20Union%20government.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20legal%20obligation%2C%20this%20discretionary%20approach%20has%20led%20to%20significant%20variation%20in%20the%20pension%20amounts%20received%20by%20beneficiaries%20across%20states%20and%20Union%20territories%20(UTs).%20State%20contributions%20range%20from%20Rs.%2050%20to%20Rs.%202300%20per%20month%20in%20some%20states%20while%20others%20contribute%20no%20amount%20at%20all.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20is%20crucial%20for%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20allocate%20a%20substantial%20amount%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Findias-elderly-wait-for-monthly-pension-to-hike-from-rs-300%2Farticleshow%2F93249996.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexceeding%20Rs%20200%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20to%20ensure%20that%20pensioners%20receive%20a%20sufficient%20sum%20irrespective%20of%20the%20contribution%20from%20the%20states.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETypically%20%E2%80%98core%20of%20the%20core%E2%80%99%20CSS%20have%20a%20fiscal%20sharing%20ratio%20of%C2%A0%2020%3A80%2C%2025%3A75%2C%20or%20even%2040%3A60%2C%20wherein%20the%20Union%20government%20predominantly%20shoulders%20the%20financial%20burden.%20However%2C%20the%20NSAP%20is%20an%20exception%20to%20this%20norm%20where%20the%20fiscal%20responsibility%20has%20been%20shifted%20to%20the%20states.%20Across%2036%20states%20and%20UTs%2C%20the%20trend%20indicates%20that%20a%20significant%20number%20of%20the%20states%20are%20contributing%20between%205%20to%2010%20times%20the%20recommended%20amount.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184550%2Funnamed-3.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22828%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184550%2Funnamed-3.png%20828w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184550%2Funnamed-3-300x288.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695274%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22794%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERTI%20Reply%20from%20MoRD%3A%C2%A0%20State%20and%20central%20contribution%20to%20major%20sub-schemes%20under%20NSAP%3Cbr%3E*RTI%20Reply%20from%20August%202023%2C%20since%20then%20pension%20amounts%20may%20have%20increased%20in%20some%20states%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EExclusions%3A%20coverage%2C%20eligibility%20and%20proactive%20identification%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECentral%20assistance%20to%20states%20and%20UTs%20under%20NSAP%20is%20determined%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20BPL%20population%20of%20the%20state.%20For%20calculating%20the%20estimated%20number%20of%20beneficiaries%20under%20each%20scheme%20for%20each%20state%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20relies%20on%20the%20population%20figures%20of%20the%202011%20Socio%20Economic%20and%20Caste%20Census.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20with%20the%20delay%20in%20the%202021%20census%20and%20the%20failure%20of%20state%20governments%20to%20proactively%20identify%20and%20enlist%20new%20beneficiaries%2C%20the%20information%20on%20eligible%20beneficiaries%20used%20to%20determine%20the%20expenditure%20under%20NSAP%20does%20not%20precisely%20capture%20the%20actual%20beneficiaries.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMoreover%2C%20BPL%20lists%20are%20susceptible%20to%20inaccuracies%20and%20errors.%20A%20recent%20investigation%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reporters-collective.in%2Fprojects%2Fai-series%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EReporters%E2%80%99%20Collective%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20revealed%20that%20the%20Family%20Identity%20Data%20Repository%2C%20an%20algorithm%20used%20by%20the%20Haryana%20government%20to%20assess%20the%20eligibility%20of%20beneficiaries%20under%20welfare%20schemes%2C%20incorrectly%20deemed%20numerous%20eligible%20individuals%20across%20NSAP%20as%20ineligible%20due%20to%20inaccurate%20data%20entry%20or%20wrong%20predictions%20by%20the%20algorithm.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20exclusion%20resulting%20from%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20enlist%20beneficiaries%2C%20many%20elderly%20individuals%20also%20experience%20exclusion%20due%20to%20the%20fixed%20quota%20imposed%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20for%20each%20state%20on%20the%20number%20of%20beneficiaries%20enrolled%20under%20the%20IGNOAPS.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20latest%20edition%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findia.unfpa.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fpub-pdf%2F20230926_india_ageing_report_2023_web_version_.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20Ageing%20Report%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Eestimates%20that%20the%20elderly%20population%20in%20the%20country%20stands%20at%2014.9%20crore%20(as%20per%202022%20estimates).%20Of%20this%2C%20two-fifths%2C%20constituting%205.96%20crore%20individuals%2C%20belong%20to%20the%20poorest%20wealth%20quintile.%20Among%20this%20group%2C%2018.7%25%2C%20or%20close%20to%201%20crore%20individuals%2C%20report%20having%20no%20source%20of%20income%20and%20face%20extreme%20financial%20vulnerability.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Finterim-union-budget-2024-nirmala-sitharaman%5C%22%3EUnion%20Budget%3A%20Revised%20Fiscal%20Deficit%205.8%25%20in%20Current%20Year%2C%20Expected%20to%20Be%205.1%25%20in%202024-25%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20states%20such%20as%20Rajasthan%20and%20Bihar%2C%20where%20the%20state%20government%20provides%20near-universal%20pensions%2C%20the%20fiscal%20burden%20is%20borne%20by%20the%20state%20exchequer.%20The%20number%20of%20beneficiaries%20receiving%20old%20age%20pensions%20in%20these%20states%20alone%20amounts%20to%20Rs%2059%20lakhs%20and%2036%20lakhs%2C%20respectively%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20national%20coverage%20of%20Rs%202.21%20crore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20NSAP%20Guidelines%20establish%20strict%20age%20criteria%20for%20IGNWPS%2C%20which%20limits%20central%20government%20assistance%20to%20widows%20aged%2040%20and%20above.%20Although%20some%20states%20have%20lowered%20this%20age%20requirement%2C%20central%20assistance%20to%20states%20is%20only%20provided%20to%20women%20who%20meet%20the%20age%20requirement%20of%20the%20specified%20guidelines.%20This%20stringent%20age%20criteria%20hinders%20single%20women%20below%20the%20age%20of%2040%2C%20who%20are%20frequently%20the%20primary%20earners%20for%20their%20families%2C%20from%20receiving%20meaningful%20income%20assistance.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFurthermore%2C%20in%20many%20states%2C%20the%20IGNWPS%20is%20limited%20to%20women%20below%20the%20age%20of%2060%20after%20which%20they%20become%20eligible%20for%20old-age%20pensions.%20For%20example%2C%20in%20Delhi%2C%20due%20to%20fixed%20caps%20in%20IGNOAPS%2C%20applications%20for%20old-age%20pensions%20have%20not%20been%20accepted%20since%202018.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20women%20above%20the%20age%20of%2060%20find%20themselves%20without%20any%20financial%20support.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilarly%2C%20according%20to%20the%202014%20guidelines%2C%20financial%20assistance%20is%20extended%20to%20individuals%20with%20a%20disability%20level%20of%2080%25%20or%20more%20under%20the%20IGNDPS.%20This%20criteria%20inadvertently%20leads%20to%20exclusion%20as%20it%20disregards%20individuals%20with%20disabilities%20below%20the%20cut%20off%20who%20may%20still%20face%20significant%20challenges%20and%20require%20monetary%20support.%20It%20is%20crucial%20to%20align%20these%20criteria%20with%20the%20definitions%20of%20persons%20with%20disabilities%20as%20outlined%20in%20The%20Rights%20of%20Persons%20with%20Disabilities%20Act%2C%202016%2C%20which%20recognises%20individuals%20with%20disabilities%20as%20those%20with%20a%20disability%20level%20of%2040%25%20or%20more.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAddressing%20the%20lack%20of%20proactive%20beneficiary%20identification%20and%20eliminating%20exclusionary%20criteria%20is%20essential%20for%20obtaining%20a%20more%20precise%20estimate%20of%20individuals%20requiring%20social%20security%20measures.%20The%202014%20guidelines%20aspire%20to%20achieve%20universal%20coverage%20in%20the%20BPL%20category%20through%20NSAP.%20However%2C%20due%20to%20existing%20budget%20and%20policy%20constraints%2C%20the%20programme%20is%20currently%20functioning%20in%20a%20demand-driven%20mode%2C%20wherein%20benefits%20are%20given%20only%20to%20those%20who%20apply%20for%20it%2C%20hindering%20the%20realisation%20of%20its%20envisioned%20universal%20coverage.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESocial%20security%20pensions%20play%20a%20crucial%20role%20in%20ensuring%20financial%20security%20and%20well-being%2C%20their%20adequacy%20and%20accessibility%20directly%20impact%20the%20socio-economic%20stability%20of%20vulnerable%20individuals.%20The%20longstanding%20demand%20of%20people%E2%80%99s%20movements%20has%20been%20that%20a%20universal%20and%20non-contributory%20minimum%20monthly%20pension%20equal%20to%2050%25%20of%20the%20minimum%20wage%20must%20be%20established%20that%20is%20periodically%20adjusted%20to%20inflation.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESimilar%20to%20the%20Minimum%20Guaranteed%20Income%20Bill%2C%202023%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20the%20NSAP%20should%20be%20legislated%20into%20an%20Act%2C%20thereby%20securing%20the%20necessary%20legal%20protections%20that%20are%20afforded%20to%20other%20welfare%20rights%20such%20as%20the%20National%20Food%20Security%20Act%20and%20the%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20National%20Rural%20Employment%20Guarantee%20Act.%20Social%20security%20pensions%20are%20not%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Erevdis%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20but%20central%20to%20the%20rights-based%20approach%20enshrined%20in%20the%20Directive%20Principles%20of%20State%20Policy%20to%20ensure%20minimum%20conditions%20for%20people%20to%20live%20with%20dignity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3EAsmi%20Sharma%20is%20associated%20with%20Jan%20Sarokar%20and%20the%20Pension%20Parishad%20Campaign.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706807808000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01184522%2Funnamed.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fbudget-2024-how-the-modi-government-has-neglected-social-security-pensions-once-again%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20is%20an%20urgent%20need%20to%20review%20the%20National%20Social%20Assistance%20Programme%20for%20it%20to%20be%20effective%20and%20meaningful.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fbudget-2024-how-the-modi-government-has-neglected-social-security-pensions-once-again%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22KKR%2C%202%20other%20entities%20sell%20Indus%20Towers'%20share%20worth%20Rs%203%2C978%20crore%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706807269000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2017-07%2F24%2Ffull%2F1500841325-3245.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fkkr-