itled-design-9.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20While%20dismissing%20a%20case%20against%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20two%20other%20cabinet%20officials%20on%20grounds%20of%20jurisdiction%2C%20a%20US%20federal%20court%20in%20California%20observed%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cplausible%E2%80%9D%20that%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20operations%20in%20Gaza%20amount%20to%20genocide%20and%20hoped%20that%20the%20US%20administration%20would%20review%20their%20%E2%80%9Cunflagging%E2%80%9D%20support%20for%20Israeli%20military%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20November%2C%20a%20non-profit%20group%20Defence%20for%20Children%20International-Palestine%20and%20nine%20individuals%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20President%20Biden%2C%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken%20and%20Secretary%20of%20Defence%20Lloyd%20Austin%20for%20supporting%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20military%20actions%20in%20Gaza%20which%20began%20in%20retaliation%20for%20Hamas%E2%80%99s%20terror%20attack%20of%20October%207%2C%20in%20violation%20of%20the%20Genocide%20convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiffs%2C%20which%20included%20individuals%20who%20are%20Palestinian%20residents%20of%20Gaza%20as%20well%20as%20US%20citizens%20with%20relatives%20in%20Gaza%2C%20had%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20compel%20the%20US%20president%20and%20government%20officials%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctake%20all%20measures%20within%20their%20power%20to%20prevent%20Israel%20from%20committing%20genocide%20against%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%9D.%20They%20also%20had%20asked%20the%20US%20to%20stop%20any%20further%20assistance%2C%20military%2C%20financial%20or%20diplomatic%2C%20to%20Israel%2C%20which%20was%20also%20sought%20as%20a%20preliminary%20injunction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20attacks%20on%20South%20Israel%2C%20Hamas%20killed%20over%201%2C400%20people%20and%20took%20around%20240%20others%20hostage.%20In%20retaliation%2C%20Israel%20launched%20multi-pronged%20bombardment%20of%20Gaza%2C%20which%20has%20killed%20over%2025%2C000%20people%2C%20mostly%20women%20and%20children%2C%20as%20per%20UN%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20government%20moved%20to%20dismiss%20the%20lawsuit%20on%20January%2026%2C%20noting%20that%20the%20US%20Constitution%20%E2%80%9Csquarely%20commits%20foreign%20policy%20and%20national%20security%20decisions%20to%20the%20political%20branches%20of%20the%20Government%E2%80%9D.%20It%20was%20also%20argued%20that%20it%20was%20not%20within%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20hand%20to%20redress%20the%20harms%20suffered%20by%20the%20plaintiffs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGranting%20the%20US%20government%E2%80%99s%20motion%20of%20dismissal%2C%20Senior%20District%20Judge%20Jeffrey%20S.%20White%20at%20the%20US%20District%20Court%20of%20Northern%20District%20of%20California%20said%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cbound%20by%20precedent%20and%20the%20division%20of%20our%20coordinate%20branches%20of%20government%20to%20abstain%20from%20exercising%20jurisdiction%20in%20this%20matter%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20US%20federal%20judge%20also%20noted%2C%20referencing%20a%20recent%20decision%20from%20the%20UN%E2%80%99s%20highest%20judicial%20body%2C%20that%20there%20was%20credibility%20to%20the%20claim%20that%20Israeli%20actions%20might%20be%20considered%20as%20genocide.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CYet%2C%20as%20the%20ICJ%20has%20found%2C%20it%20is%20plausible%20that%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20conduct%20amounts%20to%20genocide.%20This%20Court%20implores%20Defendants%20to%20examine%20the%20results%20of%20their%20unflagging%20support%20of%20the%20military%20siege%20against%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20judgement%20written%20on%20January%2031.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20District%20Judge%20White%20wrote%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Cundisputed%E2%80%9D%20evidence%20during%20the%20hearings%20that%20lined%20up%20with%20the%20ICJ%20order%20and%20%E2%80%9Cindicates%20that%20the%20current%20treatment%20of%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%20by%20the%20Israeli%20military%20may%20plausibly%20constitute%20a%20genocide%20in%20violation%20of%20international%20law%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBoth%20the%20uncontroverted%20testimony%20of%20the%20Plaintiffs%20and%20the%20expert%20opinion%20proffered%20at%20the%20hearing%20on%20these%20motions%20as%20well%20as%20statements%20made%20by%20various%20officers%20of%20the%20Israeli%20government%20indicate%20that%20the%20ongoing%20military%20siege%20in%20Gaza%20is%20intended%20to%20eradicate%20a%20whole%20people%20and%20therefore%20plausibly%20falls%20within%20the%20international%20prohibition%20against%20genocide%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fccrjustice.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fattach%2F2024%2F01%2F91_1-31-24_Order-granting-MTD_w.pdf%5C%22%3Esaid%20the%20US%20federal%20judge%20on%20Wednesday%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Hague-based%20International%20Court%20of%20Justice%20had%20refused%20to%20dismiss%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20case%20against%20Israel%2C%20stating%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icj-cij.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fcase-related%2F192%2F192-20240126-ord-01-00-en.pdf%5C%22%3Eplausible%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20that%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20behaviour%20after%20October%207%20could%20be%20viewed%20through%20the%20lens%20of%20the%20Genocide%20Convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReferring%20to%20statement%20made%20by%20Israeli%20leaders%20and%20assessments%20of%20UN%20officials%2C%20the%20ICJ%20had%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20the%20Court%E2%80%99s%20view%2C%20the%20facts%20and%20circumstances%20mentioned%20above%20are%20sufficient%20to%20conclude%20that%20at%20least%20some%20of%20the%20rights%20claimed%20by%20South%20Africa%20and%20for%20which%20it%20is%20seeking%20protection%20are%20plausible.%20This%20is%20the%20case%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20right%20of%20the%20Palestinians%20in%20Gaza%20to%20be%20protected%20from%20acts%20of%20genocide%20and%20related%20prohibited%20acts.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20provisional%20measures%2C%20the%20court%20had%20directed%20Israel%20to%20take%20all%20measures%20to%20ensure%20that%20its%20military%20does%20not%20commit%20acts%20violating%20the%20Convention%2C%20but%20had%20stopped%20short%20of%20ordering%20a%20cessation%20of%20hostilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706788809000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F22175839%2FUntitled-design-9.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fus-court-dismisses-suit-against-biden-but-says-israels-actions-plausibly-fall-under-genocide-convention%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20plaintiffs%2C%20which%20included%20individuals%20who%20are%20Palestinian%20residents%20of%20Gaza%20as%20well%20as%20US%20citizens%20with%20relatives%20in%20Gaza%2C%20had%20asked%20the%20court%20to%20compel%20the%20US%20president%20and%20government%20officials%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctake%20all%20measures%20within%20their%20power%20to%20prevent%20Israel%20from%20committing%20genocide%20against%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20of%20Gaza%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fus-court-dismisses-suit-against-biden-but-says-israels-actions-plausibly-fall-under-genocide-convention%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ladakh%3A%20China's%20PLA%20Imposes%20Restrictions%20on%20Where%20Tribal%20People%20Can%20Graze%20Livestock%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01164821%2FGFGBD9lXcAAfLGm.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20People%E2%80%99s%20Liberation%20Army%20(PLA)%20has%20imposed%20restrictions%20on%20the%20highlands%20in%20the%20Kakjung%20area%20of%20Ladakh%20which%20have%20been%20traditionally%20used%20by%20the%20tribal%20people%20for%20grazing%20their%20livestock.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20disclosure%20comes%20days%20after%20Ladakhi%20tribesmen%20and%20the%20Chinese%20army%20personnel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fladakh-local-herders-clash-with-chinese-solders-over-access-to-grazing-land%5C%22%3Eclashed%20at%20Patrolling%20Point%2035%2C%2036%20and%2037%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Kakjung%20area%20of%20Chushul%20sector%2C%20which%20has%20seen%20increasing%20tensions%20following%20the%202020%20Galwan%20Valley%20clash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIshey%20Spalzang%2C%20the%20in-charge%20councillor%20of%20Nyoma%20constituency%20of%20Ladakh%20where%20the%20clash%20took%20place%20on%20January%202%2C%20said%20that%20the%20herdsmen%20involved%20in%20the%20clash%20have%20been%20reportedly%20ordered%20by%20PLA%20soldiers%20to%20keep%20their%20livestock%20away%20from%20some%20parts%20of%20Kakjung%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Chinese%20forces%20have%20pushed%20the%20boundary%20further%20downwards%20and%20the%20herdsmen%20have%20been%20asked%20not%20to%20venture%20into%20the%20areas%20which%20were%20traditionally%20used%20as%20a%20grazing%20ground.%20They%20(PLA)%20are%20claiming%20the%20area%20as%20their%20own%2C%E2%80%9D%20Spalzang%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20do%20animals%20know%20about%20the%20border%20when%20there%20is%20no%20fence!%20The%20area%20is%20very%20close%20to%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control.%20We%20have%20asked%20the%20administration%20to%20raise%20the%20issue%20with%20the%20PLA%20so%20that%20our%20herdsmen%20can%20continue%20grazing%20their%20livestock%20there.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESources%20said%20that%20a%20meeting%20was%20held%20by%20the%20Army%20and%20Ladakh%E2%80%99s%20civil%20administration%20on%20January%2013%20where%20the%20face-off%20between%20the%20herdsmen%20and%20Chinese%20forces%20was%20discussed%20and%20several%20security%20measures%20were%20proposed%20for%20ensuring%20that%20the%20herdsmen%20don%E2%80%99t%20lose%20access%20to%20their%20traditional%20pastures.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20herdsmen%20have%20been%20assured%20that%20the%20Army%20and%20Indo-Tibetan%20Police%20Force%20personnel%20will%20accompany%20them%20and%20provide%20them%20protection%20in%20case%20such%20incidents%20happen%20in%20the%20future.%20The%20administration%20is%20committed%20to%20protecting%20livelihoods%2C%E2%80%9D%20sources%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Army%20has%20not%20officially%20reacted%20to%20the%20clash%20in%20Kakjung%2C%20its%20Ladakh-based%20Fire%20and%20Fury%20Corps%20shared%20on%20Twitter%20a%20few%20adulatory%20posts%20of%20Konchok%20Stanzin%2C%20councillor%20of%20Ladakh%E2%80%99s%20Chushul%20constituency%2C%20who%20lauded%20the%20Army%20for%20facilitating%20herdsmen%20in%20the%20highlands%20of%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Fire%20and%20Fury%20Corps%20also%20shared%20a%20video%20post%20of%20Stanzin%20which%20showed%20a%20shepherd%20saluting%20the%20cameraperson%20while%20expressing%20gratitude%20to%20the%20Indian%20Army.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20getting%20all%20the%20help%20from%20the%20Indian%20Army.%20Thank%20you%20Indian%20Army.%20Bharat%20Mata%20Ki%20Jai%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tashi%20Namgail%2C%20the%20shepherd%2C%20is%20heard%20saying%20in%20the%2017-second%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20has%20cornered%20the%20Union%20government%20on%20the%20clash%20in%20Kakjung%2C%20with%20senior%20Congress%20leader%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20stating%20that%20it%20%E2%80%9Cexposed%20the%20hollowness%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20which%20has%20been%20allegedly%20complicit%20in%20attempting%20to%20%E2%80%9Ccover%20up%20the%20worst%20territorial%20setback%20in%20six%20decades%20for%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CShot%20in%20January%202024%2C%20the%20video%20shows%20PLA%20troops%20accompanied%20by%20an%20armoured%20vehicle%20harassing%20and%20blocking%20shepherds%E2%80%99%20access%20to%20grazing%20areas%20near%20Patrolling%20Points%2035%20and%2036%20in%20the%20Chushul%20sector%20that%20lie%20well%20within%20India%E2%80%99s%20claim%20line.%20Indian%20authorities%20have%20reportedly%20asked%20the%20shepherds%20not%20to%20return%20to%20the%20area%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20official%20data%2C%20Ladakh%20has%20a%20population%20of%205.69%20lakh%20goats%20and%20sheep%2C%20most%20of%20whom%20are%20raised%20on%20the%20pastures%20in%20the%20highlands%20of%20the%20arid%20desert%20region.%20These%20includes%20the%20famed%20Changthangi%20goats%20whose%20wool%20is%20processed%20to%20make%20the%20famed%20Kashmiri%20Pashmina%20shawl.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENyoma%20councillor%20Spalzang%20said%20that%20the%20Kakjung%20area%20hosts%20about%2070%2C000%20goats%20and%20sheep%20for%20two%20months%20during%20the%20grazing%20period%2C%20which%20starts%20in%20November%20or%20December%2C%20after%20which%20the%20tribal%20families%20associated%20with%20the%20trade%20start%20their%20downward%20migration%20towards%20the%20areas%20in%20the%20plains%20of%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20similar%20incident%20had%20happened%20earlier%20also%20in%20Kakjung%20Valley.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20the%20administration%20had%20facilitated%20the%20tribal%20families%20by%20setting%20up%20two%20stone%20shelters%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20Chinese%20forces%20have%20been%20raising%20objections%20to%20these%20structures.%20%E2%80%9CThese%20restrictions%20directly%20impact%20the%20livelihoods%20of%20herdsmen%2C%E2%80%9D%20Spalzang%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20incident%20in%20Kakjung%20took%20place%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20border%20talks%20between%20the%20two%20South%20Asian%20giants%20have%20failed%20to%20make%20any%20significant%20breakthrough.%20Indo-China%20bilateral%20relations%20are%20on%20a%20downward%20spiral%20as%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20proximity%20with%20Washington%20continues%20to%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20deadly%20Galwan%20Valley%20clashes%20in%20Ladakh%20in%202020%2C%20India%20and%20China%20have%20been%20holding%20bilateral%20talks%20at%20the%20military%20level%20to%20resolve%20the%20dispute%20along%20the%20tense%20border.%20In%20his%20statement%2C%20the%20Congress%20leader%20Ramesh%20alleged%20that%20Chinese%20troops%20%E2%80%9Ccontinue%20to%20deny%20Indian%20patrols%20access%20to%20the%20strategic%20Depsang%20Plains%2C%20Demchok%20and%20other%20areas%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CChina%20continues%20to%20deny%20us%20access%20to%202%2C000%20square%20km%20despite%2018%20rounds%20of%20military%20talks%2C%E2%80%9D%20Ramesh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20Chinese%20forces%20objected%20to%20the%20presence%20of%20Ladakhi%20herdsmen%20at%20the%20Demchok%20sector%20within%20India%E2%80%99s%20perception%20of%20the%20LAC%2C%20which%20was%20followed%20by%20meetings%20between%20the%20commanders%20of%20the%20two%20armies.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706787012000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F01164821%2FGFGBD9lXcAAfLGm.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fladakh-chinas-pla-imposes-restrictions-on-where-tribal-people-can-graze-livestock%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Herdsmen%20involved%20in%20the%20January%202%20clash%20with%20the%20PLA%20have%20been%20reportedly%20ordered%20by%20PLA%20soldiers%20to%20keep%20their%20livestock%20away%20from%20some%20parts%20of%20Kakjung%20Valley.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Funcategorised%2Fladakh-chinas-pla-imposes-restrictions-on-where-tribal-people-can-graze-livestock%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22European%20Union%20agrees%20on%20a%20new%2050%20billion-euro%20aid%20package%20for%20Ukraine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706785921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2